Parliament, Tuesday, 27 August 2019 – The Passenger Rail Agency of South Africa (Prasa) and the Rail Safety Regulator will today brief the Portfolio Committee on Transport on their annual performance plans. The committee is on a week-long oversight programme in Gauteng. The programme also creates an opportunity for members of the committee to familiarise themselves with the Department of Transport’s entities. Meeting details are as follows: Time: 9 am
	Venue: RSR Office, Lake Buena Vista Building, 1 Gordon Hood Avenue, Centurion
	Entity: Rail Safety Regulator Time: 12 noon
	Venue: Dunnotar, Nigel (Ekurhuleni)
	Entity: Prasa ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON, MR MOSEBENZI ZWANE. For media enquiries please contact the committee’s Media Officer: Name: Sibongile Maputi (Mr)
	Parliamentary Communication Services
	Tel: 021 403 8041
	Cell: 081 052 6060
